In this reporting period, the GICHD continued the coordination of 6 Technical Working Groups responsible for the review of:
- IMAS 04.10 - Glossary of Mine Action Terms, Definitions and Abbreviations;
- IMAS 05.10 - Information Management for Mine Action, (Annex B-Minimum Data Requirements);
- IMAS 06.10 - Management of Training;
- IMAS 08.40 - Marking Mine and ERW Hazards;
- TNMA 10.10/01 - Management of Human Remains located during Mine Action Operations; and
- TNMA 12.10/01 Risk Education for Improvised Explosive Devices.

The Tests and Evaluation Protocols for EOD competencies and for IEDD competencies as well as the IMAS 09.30 on EOD and the Test and Evaluation Protocols on Animal Detection Systems testing and testing sites have been revised and approved by the IMAS Review Board.
The TWG responsible for the review of IMAS 04.10 submitted normative guidance on the management of terminology to be included in IMAS 04.10. The TWG on the management of human remains has also submitted an IMAS chapter to the IMAS Review Board.
The GICHD will continue to coordinate these Technical Working Groups till the end of the year.
